meanings.definition: A group or set of nine.
meanings.sent1: The enneads of colorful balloons floated in the sky.
meanings.sent2: She collected enneads of seashells on the beach.
meanings.sent3: The enneads of puppies made quite a chaotic mess in the yard.
meanings.sent4: Her enneads of laughter filled the room with joy.
meanings.sent5: The enneads of stars in the night sky twinkled brightly.

meanings.sent1: The enneads of books on the shelf caught her attention.

meanings.sent3: The enneads of cupcakes disappeared quickly at the party.
meanings.sent4: The enneads of waves crashing on the shore sounded like music.
meanings.sent5: The enneads of colors in the painting blended harmoniously.
